# {{app_name}} Project Structure

This is a Flutter mobile application built with a feature-based architecture.

## Project Overview

- **Framework**: Flutter 3.38.0+
- **Language**: Dart 3.8.1+
- **State Management**: Riverpod 3.0.3 (with code generation)
- **Routing**: GoRouter 17.0.0
- **Local Database**: Sembast 3.8.5+2
- **HTTP Client**: Dio 5.9.0
- **Responsive Design**: Flutter ScreenUtil 5.9.3

## Directory Structure

The main source code is located in `lib/src/`:

- **`app.dart`**: Main application widget with MaterialApp.router setup
- **`common_widget/`**: Reusable widgets used across features
- **`constant/`**: App constants (assets, error messages, etc.)
- **`core/`**: Core mixins and utilities (router_mixin, startup_mixin, etc.)
- **`feature/`**: Feature modules organized by domain
- **`localization/`**: Localization files and providers (en, id)
- **`routing/`**: GoRouter configuration and route definitions
- **`service/`**: Services (Firebase, notifications)
- **`theme/`**: App theming (colors, text styles, sizes)
- **`utils/`**: Utility functions and configurations

## Feature Module Structure

Each feature in `lib/src/feature/` follows this structure:

```
feature_name/
  ├── data/
  │   ├── feature_repository.dart        # Repository implementation
  │   └── feature_repository.g.dart      # Generated Riverpod providers
  ├── domain/
  │   └── *.dart                         # Domain models/entities
  └── presentation/
      ├── feature_screen.dart            # Main screen widget
      ├── feature_subscreen.dart         # Sub-screen widgets
      ├── controller/
      │   ├── feature_event.dart         # Navigation/action mixins
      │   └── feature_state.dart         # State management mixins
      └── widget/                        # Feature-specific widgets
```

## Entry Points

- **`main_dev.dart`**: Development flavor entry point
- **`main_stg.dart`**: Staging flavor entry point
- **`main_prod.dart`**: Production flavor entry point
- **`initializer.dart`**: App initialization logic
- **`flavor.dart`**: Flavor configuration

## Flavors

The app supports three flavors:
- **dev**: Development environment (`{{app_id}}.dev`)
- **stg**: Staging environment (`{{app_id}}.stg`)
- **prod**: Production environment (`{{app_id}}`)

Flavor configuration is in [pubspec.yaml](mdc:pubspec.yaml) under `flavorizr`.

